               <msContents>
                  <summary>This Persian translation <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6886">Lubāb
                     al-Akhbār</title> (Kernels of Reports), originally compiled in Arabic by <persName key="person_f502"
                        role="ant com">Aḥmad ibn ‘Abdullāh</persName>, was translated into Persian by
                     more than one translator, who name appears here as <persName role="trl" key="person_f2579"
                        >Muḥammad Maḥmūd Muḥammad</persName>. The present manuscript contains the
                     original Arabic with paraphrased Persian translations divided into forty
                     chapters, with each chapter containing ten traditions. However, chapter 3
                     contains eleven traditions, while chapters 19 and 38 have nine traditions each,
                     whereas the heading sequence in chapter 12 appears inconsistent.</summary>
